Cell.Text: S|What happened? What did you see? Different people have very different experiences when reading these books.
Did you actually learn what you needed to know by reading that Black Book?

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ05NelothGreetTopic: I talked to Hermaeus Mora.

Cell.Text: You're still acting surprisingly sane, too. What did he have to say? He must have wanted something from you.

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ05NelothGreetA1: I talked to Hermaeus Mora.

Cell.Text: [S] G|That's a fairly common experience, at least for those who remain coherent enough to report what they've seen. | You were in Apocrypha. Or at least your consciousness was - your body remained here of course. | You should read the book again until you reach what appears to be the "end" - then you will have fully understood the knowledge it contains.

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ05NelothGreetA2: I found myself in another place.

Cell.Text: No wonder the Dwemer were so interested in that book. It must have been one that Miraak used to advance his power as Dragonborn. | But I assume there's some bad news. It would be unlike Hermaeus Mora to allow anyone to gain such knowledge without exacting a price.

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ05NelothGreetA3: I learned the second Word of the Bend Will Shout.

Cell.Text: [S] G|Hmph. What secrets could they have worth keeping from old Mora? Sounds like a bargain to me. | Hermaeus Mora learns some fascinating new ways to skin a horker, and you become the second most powerful Dragonborn that ever lived.

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ05NelothGreetB1: He wants the "secrets of the Skaal" in exchange for teaching me the third Word.

Cell.Text: [S] G|You ducked out of the middle of a conversation with old Mora himself? Mighty impertinent of you! | And, since you need secrets that only Hermaeus Mora knows, it seems like a rather foolish thing to do. But I'm sure you know best.

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ05NelothGreetB2: I don't know yet what he wanted. I left Apocrypha before I found out.

Cell.Text: [S] S|You must talk to Storn, then. As shaman, he is the keeper of such lore. | I have learned some of what he knows, but it is not my place to divulge anything to an outsider.

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ05FreaSecretsTopicTopic: I need the "secrets of the Skaal" in order to defeat Miraak.

Cell.Text: G|You will not convince me to betray Storn's trust. Talk to him. He will decide the matter.

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ05FreaSecretsA1: Aren't you his apprentice? He must have taught you his secrets...

Cell.Text: G|Good. Although I do not think he will help you. These secrets are sacred to us.

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ05FreaSecretsA2: I understand. I'll talk to Storn.

Cell.Text: [S] Here is the foul book that killed Storn. Take it away from here. Throw it into the sea. It is evil.
G|I think he knew what would happen. He saw his death in that book.
G|Do not let his death be for nothing. Go and stop Miraak.
G|I do not blame you. I know he chose this. I just wish he had seen another way.
G|Leave me to mourn my father. I have no more words for you now.

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ05FreaGiveBookTopic: What do you need?

Cell.Text: G|What have you done?
G|What's happening? You must stop it!
G|Be silent.

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ05FreaBlockingTopic

Cell.Text: G|What does it mean? What was that? What happened to him?
G|He was a good man. The strong center of the Skaal. If you know how to stop whatever that was, go and stop it.
G|These are dark times. How will we get through them without Storn to guide us?
G|You will stop... whatever that was - so that that evil does not swallow the Skaal like it did Storn?
G|Frea will grieve, but she will prove a good shaman. Storn taught her well. He knew she was ready to guide us in his place.
G|Storn was like a father to me. To all of us. I do not know what we will do without him.
G|Whatever that was... I trust you will make it pay for what it did to Storn.
G|I don't understand. I thought the village was safe. What are we going to do now?
G|You brought this thing into our village. I do not know why Storn trusted you, but he did. Make sure he did not die for nothing.
G|A manifestation of Hermaeus Mora... that book Storn was reading, I've read vague hints of them, but never thought to actually see...
G|He has returned to the All-Maker. He is at peace now, no matter what that evil thing may have done to his body.
G|Oh... so terrible. When will these dark times be over?
G|Leave us to grieve.
G|Leave me alone.
G|Terrible times.
G|Leave us now.
G|What next? When will it stop?
G|Go and do what you must.
G|Leave us, please.
G|Go. Let us mourn him in our own way.
G|Poor Storn. I can't believe it.
G|Leave us now.
G|This is all too much for me.
G|Go and avenge him.
G|What's happening?
G|What's happening to Storn?
G|By the All-Maker!
G|What is that?
G|All-Maker save us!
G|Stay back!
G|Storn! What is he doing?
G|What have you brought into our village?
G|All-Maker, please help him!
G|Someone do something!
G|By the gods... I can't believe...
G|No, it cannot be...

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ05SkaalBlockingTopic

Cell.Text: We know him as Herma-Mora, the Demon of Knowledge. It is in his nature to hoard secrets to himself. Their value to him is of no consequence. | The very fact that the Skaal have kept knowledge from him has merely increased his desire to have it.

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ05StornSecretsA3: Why would Hermaeus Mora want your secrets?

Cell.Text: [S] So it falls to me to be the one to give up the secrets to our ancient enemy. I do not know if I have the strength to face him. | With Miraak's corruption of the Stones... the Oneness of the land is disrupted, and our connection to the All-Maker is broken.

[S] So it falls to me to be the one to give up the secrets to our ancient enemy. I do not know if I have the strength to face him. | The Tree Stone is still corrupted... the land is still out of balance. But with the other five restored... it may be enough. It will have to be.

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ05StornSecrets_A1: He said it's the only way he'll teach me the final Word of Miraak's Shout.

Cell.Text: [S] Yes. The Skaal also tell of the day when we must finally give up our secrets. When Herma-Mora finally wins. | As shaman, it is my duty to guard these secrets, but also to decide when it is necessary to give them up. | I believe that time is now. If I am wrong, may my ancestors forgive me.

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ05StornSecrets_B2: You mean you'll give him what he wants?

Cell.Text: [S] G|It may. It should. And I will think on what you ask of me, to decide if it is necessary, or just another of Herma-Mora's tricks.

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ05StornSecrets_B1: I'll restore the remaining Stones if that will help.

Cell.Text: [S] G|That is my hope as well. I am trusting that you will make this sacrifice worthwhile.

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ05StornGiveBookA1: I hope you know what you're doing. (Give book)

Cell.Text: That is our name for him - the Demon of Knowledge. He has always been our enemy.

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ05StornSecretsHermaMora: Herma-Mora? Why do you call him that?

Cell.Text: G|No... he is too strong...
G|There is nothing else to say. I am in the All-Maker's hands now.
Give me the book. I will read it, and speak to old Herma-Mora myself. I will make sure he lives up to his part of the bargain.

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ05StornGiveBookTopic: What do you need?

Cell.Text: Ancient lore, handed down from shaman to shaman since the All-Maker first gave Solstheim to the Skaal. | How to talk to the wind, how to listen to the earth - these are our secrets. Nothing of power or mastery.

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ05StornSecretsA2: What are the "secrets of the Skaal"?

Cell.Text: Are you ready to trade your secrets to Hermaeus Mora?
The Tree Stone is still corrupted... the land is still out of balance. But with the other five restored... it may be enough. It will have to be.
Are you ready to trade your secrets to Hermaeus Mora?
No... I am still too weak to face him. It will take all my strength if I am to force him to hold to his bargain. | You must cleanse the other Stones so that I can draw power from the All-Maker.

Hermaeus Mora... old Herma-Mora himself. So he is the source of Miraak's power. Of course. | We have many tales of Herma-Mora trying to trick us into giving up our secrets to him. | And now he comes again for what we have long kept from him.

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ05MQ05StornSecretsNEWTopic: I spoke to Hermaeus Mora. He asked for the "secrets of the Skaal."
